data.title: Dan Parham - Baseball

data.text:
On Parham: Versatile defensive player who can be used in the infield or the outfield ... Shows promise as a hitter who makes consistent contact and has good speed. Should compete for role as a designated hitter.

2010: Saw time in seven games during the season ... Hit .400 (2-for-5) with a run scored and a run batted in ... Struck out twice ... Made one putout and had two assists in the field ... Registered his first collegiate hit against Norfolk State with a pinch-hit, RBI single ... Went 1-for-2 with a run scored in a win over Penn.

Jenks High School: Earned three varsity letters in baseball and played one year of football as a running back, linebacker and strong safety ... Named to the Principal[apos]s Honor Roll all four years and was an AP Honors Scholar in 2009.

Personal: Born 9/24/90 in Tulsa, Okla. ... Younger of two children of William and Traci Parham ... Has an older sister, Jessica (22) ... Father rowed in college for Georgetown ... Majoring in Communication.
